        <mxCell id="note" value="PaaS inverts the multi-cloud advantage: managed-service semantics differ (Cosmos DB != DynamoDB, Azure SQL != Aurora), so you lose 'same service both sides'.&lt;br&gt;Regain parity via a neutral data layer, application dual-write, or containerizing compute (Container Apps &lt;-&gt; ECS / Fargate)." style="text;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=10;fontStyle=0;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="120" y="545" width="820" height="40" as="geometry"/></mxCell>
